==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pituitous
<hw>Pi*tu"i*tous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>pituitosus</ets>: cf. F. <ets>pituiteux</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Consisting of, or resembling, pituite or mucus; full of mucus;
discharging mucus.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Pituitous fever</b></col> <fld>(Med.)</fld>, <cd>typhoid
fever; enteric fever.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pituitrin</ent>⟦br⟧
